text: Karacha-Yelga () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Karacha-Yelginsky Selsoviet, Kushnarenkovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 600 as of 2010. There are 8 streets. == Geography == It is located 22 km from Kushnarenkovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kushnarenkovsky District
title: Karacha-Yelga
